WEBVTT

00:10.078 --> 00:11.412
- * ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR

00:11.445 --> 00:13.247
* ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX *

00:13.281 --> 00:14.515
* SHAKE IT, DUDE

00:14.548 --> 00:22.456
*

00:28.462 --> 00:29.797
* ONE, TWO, DO IT

00:29.830 --> 00:32.166
*

00:32.200 --> 00:33.601
* ONE, TWO, THREE

00:33.634 --> 00:35.403
- * FOUR, FOUR

00:35.436 --> 00:38.439
*

00:40.874 --> 00:44.078
- AND OUR NEXT CONTESTANT,
MICHAEL NOVOTNY!

00:44.112 --> 00:45.279
[cheers and applause]

00:45.313 --> 00:49.417
AND HERE COMES TED SCHMIDT!

00:49.450 --> 00:53.487
A NEW ENTRY...
JUSTIN TAYLOR!

00:53.521 --> 00:56.724
ALWAYS A FAVORITE,
BRIAN KINNEY!

00:56.757 --> 01:02.230
A REAL CROWD-PLEASER...
EMMETT HONEYCUTT!

01:02.263 --> 01:06.167
AND LET'S HEAR IT
FOR BEN BRUCKNER!

01:06.200 --> 01:07.435
[cheers and applause]

01:07.468 --> 01:13.707
AND THE WINNER IS...

01:13.741 --> 01:15.709
BRIAN KINNEY!

01:15.743 --> 01:22.082
[cheers and applause]

01:28.689 --> 01:30.591
- AAH! NO!

01:30.624 --> 01:32.760
- WHAT IS IT?

01:32.793 --> 01:36.397
- OH, I HAD THAT DREAM--
AGAIN.

01:36.430 --> 01:40.668
- THE MR. SPERM-DONOR PAGEANT?
WHO WON THIS TIME?

01:40.701 --> 01:42.136
- GUESS.

01:42.170 --> 01:44.272
- MAYBE IT'S
SOME KIND OF SIGN.

01:44.305 --> 01:47.808
- FUCK.

01:47.841 --> 01:51.345
I ALREADY TOLD YOU,
I WANT SOMEONE ELSE.

01:51.379 --> 01:52.513
- BUT WE AGREED
IT'S IMPORTANT

01:52.546 --> 01:54.248
OUR KIDS SHOULD HAVE
THE SAME PARENT.

01:54.282 --> 01:56.150
- WE DIDN'T AGREE IT SHOULD BE
THE SAME ASSHOLE.

01:56.184 --> 01:58.619
- FINE. WE'LL PULL A NAME
OUT OF A HAT.

01:58.652 --> 02:03.257
LET'S GET SOME SLEEP,
BEFORE THE ALARM GOES OFF.

02:03.291 --> 02:06.527
- LOOK, I KNOW HOW MUCH
HE MEANS TO YOU.

02:06.560 --> 02:10.764
HE ALWAYS HAS,
AND HE ALWAYS WILL.

02:10.798 --> 02:14.802
BUT HE DOESN'T MEAN
THE SAME TO ME.

02:18.939 --> 02:21.809
- TO EAT, OR NOT TO EAT?

02:21.842 --> 02:23.444
- TRY ONE.

02:23.477 --> 02:24.545
- YOU KNOW I'M TRYING
TO WATCH MY WEIGHT.

02:24.578 --> 02:27.815
- ONE'S NOT GOING TO KILL YOU.

02:27.848 --> 02:31.852
- ALL RIGHT.

02:31.885 --> 02:34.188
[gasps]

02:34.222 --> 02:35.323
[panting]

02:35.356 --> 02:37.391
WATER...

02:37.425 --> 02:39.693
WATER.

02:39.727 --> 02:40.794
WATER!

02:40.828 --> 02:43.797
OOH, GOD.

02:43.831 --> 02:45.699
MMM...

02:45.733 --> 02:47.801
JESUS! YOU SAID IT WASN'T
GOING TO KILL ME.

02:47.835 --> 02:49.203
WHAT THE HELL'S
IN THOSE THINGS?

02:49.237 --> 02:51.805
- CHILI POWDER, TABASCO,
PEPPERS...

02:51.839 --> 02:55.676
SOUPCON OF SULFURIC ACID
FOR THAT EXTRA LITTLE KICK.

02:55.709 --> 02:58.812
MEET OUR NEWEST ACCOUNT,
HOT P'TATERS.

02:58.846 --> 03:01.649
- I DEFY YOU
TO MAKE THESE SEXY.

03:06.320 --> 03:08.589
[chuckles]
THAT'S ACTUALLY...

03:08.622 --> 03:10.991
"HOTTER THAN YOUR DATE
LAST SATURDAY NIGHT."

03:11.024 --> 03:12.560
YEAH, GENIUS.

03:12.593 --> 03:13.894
- I DON'T CARE
WHAT HE'S DOING.

03:13.927 --> 03:16.230
I HAVE TO SEE HIM.
- I'M SORRY, BRIAN.

03:16.264 --> 03:17.231
UH, SHE INSISTED.

03:17.265 --> 03:18.432
- BRIAN, I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

03:18.466 --> 03:19.733
THE SCHOOL JUST CALLED.

03:19.767 --> 03:21.569
PETER BROKE HIS ARM
AT SOCCER PRACTICE.

03:21.602 --> 03:24.738
- GARDNER...
MY SISTER, CLAIRE.

03:24.772 --> 03:27.308
- IT SOUNDS LIKE YOU'RE
HAVING A FAMILY CRISIS.

03:27.341 --> 03:29.310
I'M GOING TO LET YOU
SORT IT OUT.

03:29.343 --> 03:31.312
PLEASURE.
- THANK YOU.

03:31.345 --> 03:34.315
I HAVE TO GET TO
THE EMERGENCY ROOM RIGHT AWAY.

03:34.348 --> 03:35.616
- THEN WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
- CAN YOU HELP ME?

03:35.649 --> 03:37.318
- CAN YOU LOOK AFTER JOHN?

03:37.351 --> 03:39.253
- IN CASE YOU HAVEN'T NOTICED,
I'M WORKING.

03:39.287 --> 03:41.522
- WELL, I DON'T KNOW WHAT ELSE
TO DO WITH HIM.

03:41.555 --> 03:43.657
- STICK HIM IN A LOCKER
AT THE BUS STATION.

03:43.691 --> 03:45.659
YOU EVER HEARD OF A SITTER?

03:45.693 --> 03:47.528
- YOU EXPECT ME TO FIND SOMEONE
ON A MOMENT'S NOTICE

03:47.561 --> 03:48.529
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE DAY?

03:48.562 --> 03:49.797
- LEAVE HIM WITH MOM.

03:49.830 --> 03:52.266
- MOM'S INDISPOSED.

03:52.300 --> 03:53.934
- IS SHE PASSED OUT DRUNK
ON THE FLOOR AGAIN?

03:53.967 --> 03:56.337
- BRIAN, PLEASE,
I DON'T HAVE TIME FOR THIS.

03:56.370 --> 03:58.939
- [sighs]
[video game beeps]

03:58.972 --> 04:01.375
HOW LONG WILL YOU BE?
- I DON'T KNOW,

04:01.409 --> 04:02.676
BUT I'LL CALL
AS SOON AS I HEAR.

04:02.710 --> 04:04.345
OKAY, YOU BEHAVE YOURSELF,
DO YOU HEAR ME?

04:04.378 --> 04:09.583
[game beeping]

04:14.422 --> 04:16.824
- YOU STILL A FAG?

04:16.857 --> 04:20.894
- HERE.

04:20.928 --> 04:22.396
HAVE ONE.

04:22.430 --> 04:24.532
HAVE TWO.

04:30.938 --> 04:33.541
[chuckles]

04:33.574 --> 04:34.975
- LOOK AT THAT
BONE STRUCTURE,

04:35.008 --> 04:37.445
THOSE ADORABLE SEASHELL EARS.

04:37.478 --> 04:39.947
AND HE'S INCREDIBLY TALENTED.

04:39.980 --> 04:42.916
- HE'S ONLY 19.
- WELL, ISN'T THAT A PLUS?

04:42.950 --> 04:44.518
FRESH, YOUNG SPERM?

04:44.552 --> 04:46.320
- TO ME, HE'S STILL A BABY.

04:46.354 --> 04:48.656
IT JUST DOESN'T SEEM RIGHT
HAVING A BABY WITH A BABY.

04:48.689 --> 04:50.824
- OKAY.

04:50.858 --> 04:53.461
- BEN'S BRAINY AND BRAWNY.

04:53.494 --> 04:55.796
- I'D SAY HE'S
JUST ABOUT PERFECT,

04:55.829 --> 04:57.398
EXCEPT FOR ONE THING.

04:57.431 --> 05:00.834
- RIGHT.

05:00.868 --> 05:03.704
THERE'S ALWAYS TED.

05:03.737 --> 05:06.540
- AH, GOOD OLD RELIABLE TEDDY.

05:06.574 --> 05:08.976
- EMMETT?
- YOU TRY IT.

05:09.009 --> 05:10.878
- TEDDY!

05:16.016 --> 05:18.886
- WHAT IS THIS PLACE?
- IT'S CALLED A DINER.

05:18.919 --> 05:21.689
- HEY, BRI.
GET YOURSELF A NEW BOYFRIEND?

05:21.722 --> 05:23.957
- YEAH, HE'S EVEN YOUNGER
THAN THE LAST ONE!

05:23.991 --> 05:25.693
[laughter]

05:25.726 --> 05:27.428
- GOD, I HOPE NOBODY
SEES ME.

05:27.461 --> 05:31.432
- SIT DOWN AND SHUT UP.
- WHO'S THE CUTIE?

05:31.465 --> 05:33.367
- HE'S THE SPAWN OF SATAN
AND MY SISTER.

05:33.401 --> 05:36.036
- THOUGHT I RECOGNIZED
A FAMILY RESEMBLANCE.

05:36.069 --> 05:37.838
- BOTH SIDES.

05:37.871 --> 05:42.976
- IS SHE A DRAG QUEEN?

05:43.010 --> 05:45.012
- SO, WHAT CAN I GET YA,
HONEY?

05:45.045 --> 05:46.847
- I'M NOT EATING ANYTHING
IN HERE.

05:46.880 --> 05:49.349
- BRING HIM A BURGER
WITH EXTRA GROUND GLASS.

05:51.084 --> 05:52.986
- HEY.
- HEY.

05:53.020 --> 05:54.722
- I WANT TO GO TO THE ARCADE
IN THE MALL.

05:54.755 --> 05:56.624
I GO THERE EVERY DAY
AFTER SCHOOL.

05:56.657 --> 05:58.459
- DOES YOUR MAMA KNOW?
- SHE THINKS I'M

05:58.492 --> 05:59.493
AT CHOIR PRACTICE.

05:59.527 --> 06:02.463
BET YOU'D LIKE THAT.

06:02.496 --> 06:05.466
- WHAT'RE YOU DOING
WITH YOUR NEPHEW?

06:05.499 --> 06:06.900
- I'M BRAT-SITTING.

06:06.934 --> 06:08.469
- HI, JOHN.
I'M MICHAEL.

06:08.502 --> 06:10.070
I'M BRIAN'S FRIEND.
YOU REMEMBER ME?

06:10.103 --> 06:12.039
- NO.

06:12.072 --> 06:14.041
- WHY DON'T YOU BRING HIM
BY THE STORE?

06:14.074 --> 06:15.876
I HAVE A COMIC BOOK STORE,
IF YOU WANT TO COME BY.

06:15.909 --> 06:18.512
IT'S JUST DOWN THE STREET.

06:18.546 --> 06:21.615
- YOU GOT THE NEW AVENGERS?
- I GOT EVERYTHING.

06:21.649 --> 06:23.484
- WHY DON'T YOU DROP BY
AND CHECK IT OUT?

06:23.517 --> 06:25.653
I GIVE FREE SAMPLES.

06:25.686 --> 06:27.488
- CAN WE, UNCLE BRI?

06:27.521 --> 06:31.692
- ALL OF A SUDDEN,
WE'RE RELATED.

06:31.725 --> 06:35.796
- WASN'T THAT SWEET OF MICHAEL?
- YEAH, HE'S A REAL MENSCH.

06:37.965 --> 06:41.535
AND WOULDN'T GIVE US
ANY TROUBLE.

06:47.074 --> 06:49.042
- DO YOU WANT TO HAND ME
THAT LIGHT BULB, BABE?

06:49.076 --> 06:50.644
- CAN I HAVE THIS SPIDER-MAN
TOO?

06:50.678 --> 06:53.080
- MM-HMM.
- DON'T BE SO FUCKING GREEDY.

06:53.113 --> 06:54.948
HE'S ALREADY GIVEN YOU
A SHITLOAD.

06:54.982 --> 06:56.116
- IT'S YOURS.

06:56.149 --> 06:59.052
- WHAT DO YOU SAY?

06:59.086 --> 07:01.822
- THANKS, MIKE.

07:01.855 --> 07:03.524
- YOU TWO WANT A KID?

07:03.557 --> 07:06.126
- ACTUALLY, I HAVE GIVEN THAT
SERIOUS THOUGHT...

07:06.159 --> 07:08.829
BECAUSE THE STUDIES
SHOW THAT TWO MEN

07:08.862 --> 07:10.698
ARE EVERY BIT AS CAPABLE
OF RAISING A CHILD--

07:10.731 --> 07:13.100
- PSST.
I MEAN THIS ONE.

07:13.133 --> 07:15.569
COME ON.
- AW...I DON'T WANNA GO.

07:15.603 --> 07:16.837
- WE ALL HAVE TO GO SOMETIME.

07:16.870 --> 07:18.806
- STOP PULLING ME, ASSHOLE.

07:18.839 --> 07:20.708
GODDAMN FAG.

07:20.741 --> 07:23.243
- YOU WERE GREAT WITH HIM,
YOU KNOW THAT?

07:23.276 --> 07:25.613
- KIDS LOVE ME.
DON'T ASK ME WHY.

07:25.646 --> 07:28.682
- I DON'T HAVE TO.
- GOD, YOU'RE HARD!

07:28.716 --> 07:29.750
- YEAH, YOU TOO.

07:29.783 --> 07:31.118
- [clears throat]

07:31.151 --> 07:34.154
DO YOU HAVE THE NEW SUPERMAN?

07:34.187 --> 07:37.124
- YOU'RE LOOKING AT HIM.

07:37.157 --> 07:40.828
IT'S, UH, RIGHT OVER THERE.

07:40.861 --> 07:44.131
THOSE WORKOUTS HAVE REALLY BEEN
PAYING OFF.

07:44.164 --> 07:45.999
SO I'LL SEE YOU AT DINNER?

07:46.033 --> 07:49.770
- UH, I THOUGHT WOULD, UH,
HIT THE GYM TONIGHT...

07:49.803 --> 07:52.973
PUT IN SOME EXTRA TIME
ON MY CHEST AND STOMACH.

07:53.006 --> 07:54.775
- BUT I THOUGHT
WE MADE PLANS.

07:54.808 --> 07:57.244
- SO WE'LL CHANGE THEM.
IT'S NOT A PROBLEM, IS IT?

07:57.277 --> 08:01.849
- NO.

08:01.882 --> 08:04.184
NOT A PROBLEM.

08:08.055 --> 08:09.623
[opera music playing]

08:09.657 --> 08:12.726
- YOU'RE A WONDER.

08:12.760 --> 08:13.994
- I AM?

08:14.027 --> 08:15.128
- I'VE KNOWN YOU...
HOW LONG?

08:15.162 --> 08:16.263
FIVE, SIX YEARS?

08:16.296 --> 08:17.998
I HAD NO IDEA
YOU COULD COOK.

08:18.031 --> 08:20.601
- MMM, THAT'S BECAUSE I NEVER
HAD ANYONE TO COOK FOR.

08:20.634 --> 08:24.004
NOW THAT I DO,
YOU WON'T BELIEVE THE DELIGHTS

08:24.037 --> 08:26.640
I PLAN TO WHIP UP.

08:26.674 --> 08:30.611
- WELL, I CAN HARDLY WAIT...
FOR DESSERT.

08:30.644 --> 08:32.312
- HMM. MMM.

08:32.345 --> 08:34.047
JUST A MINUTE. I JUST--
I WANT TO CLEAN UP.

08:34.081 --> 08:36.183
- EVERYTHING'S
ALREADY CLEAN.

08:36.216 --> 08:38.051
THE KITCHEN'S PRACTICALLY
SPOTLESS.

08:38.085 --> 08:39.820
- WELL, YOU KNOW ME.

08:39.853 --> 08:43.290
CAN'T RELAX UNTIL
EVERYTHING'S IN ORDER.

08:43.323 --> 08:45.158
- GOD, WHEN I COOK,

08:45.192 --> 08:47.294
THE KITCHEN LOOKS LIKE
A HURRICANE HIT.

08:47.327 --> 08:49.830
- SORRY.
- OH.

08:49.863 --> 08:52.199
- WELL, THIS'LL JUST TAKE
A SECOND.

09:01.108 --> 09:02.943
THIS IS SO NICE.

09:02.976 --> 09:04.211
- MMM.

09:04.244 --> 09:06.113
- I WISH YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO GO.

09:06.146 --> 09:08.048
- WHO'S GOING ANYWHERE?

09:08.081 --> 09:11.852
- I MEAN...IT'S SO...

09:11.885 --> 09:13.587
INCONVENIENT,
YOU ALWAYS HAVING TO RUN

09:13.621 --> 09:15.656
BACK AND FORTH
TO YOUR PLACE.

09:15.689 --> 09:18.592
- WELL, SOMETIMES ONE DOES NEED
A FRESH PAIR OF UNDIES.

09:18.626 --> 09:19.993
- YEAH, BUT WOULDN'T IT BE
MORE PRACTICAL

09:20.027 --> 09:21.261
IF THE UNDIES CAME TO YOU,

09:21.294 --> 09:25.666
RATHER THAN YOU GOING
TO THE UNDIES?

09:25.699 --> 09:27.601
- TEDDY, ARE--
ARE YOU SAYING...

09:27.635 --> 09:30.203
- WHY NOT MOVE IN?

09:30.237 --> 09:32.606
- YOU--YOU MEAN...
- LIVE TOGETHER.

09:32.640 --> 09:33.874
SHACK UP.

09:33.907 --> 09:35.342
- "SHACK UP."

09:35.375 --> 09:38.712
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED TO HEAR
THOSE WORDS.

09:40.180 --> 09:42.616
BUT DON'T YOU THINK
IT'S TOO SOON?

09:42.650 --> 09:46.386
- YEAH.
PROBABLY RIGHT.

09:46.419 --> 09:47.955
I MEAN, WE'VE ONLY
KNOWN EACH OTHER HOW LONG?

09:47.988 --> 09:49.222
FIVE, SIX YEARS?

09:49.256 --> 09:51.091
WE SHOULD WAIT AT LEAST
ANOTHER FIVE MORE.

09:51.124 --> 09:52.993
- YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

09:53.026 --> 09:54.361
LOVING SOMEONE
AND LIVING TOGETHER

09:54.394 --> 09:55.763
ARE TWO DIFFERENT THINGS.

09:55.796 --> 09:57.230
WHAT IF WE DRIVE EACH OTHER
CRAZY?

09:57.264 --> 10:01.869
- WELL...WON'T KNOW
UNLESS WE TRY.

10:01.902 --> 10:05.238
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

10:05.272 --> 10:08.041
- WELL, AS...

10:08.075 --> 10:10.711
LONG AS I WON'T BE
IN THE WAY.

10:10.744 --> 10:14.281
- HOW COULD YOU EVER BE
IN THE WAY?

10:19.152 --> 10:20.921
PUT THAT THERE.
- [laughs]

10:20.954 --> 10:23.223
- WON'T LEAVE A SPOT.

10:26.827 --> 10:29.763
- OKAY, GUS,
GIMME YOUR HAPPY FACE.

10:29.797 --> 10:33.934
NOW LET ME SEE YOUR...
SAD FACE?

10:33.967 --> 10:36.069
OOH, SAD FACE. MMM.

10:36.103 --> 10:39.406
- YOU KNOW,
YOU'RE REALLY GOOD WITH KIDS.

10:39.439 --> 10:42.743
- YEAH, GUS ADORES YOU.

10:42.776 --> 10:45.345
- THAT'S 'CAUSE I'M A PUSHOVER.
[grunts]

10:45.378 --> 10:47.280
- IT'S BECAUSE YOU'VE GOT
A GOOD HEART.

10:47.314 --> 10:49.216
- THAT'S WHAT MY MOM
ALWAYS TELLS ME.

10:49.249 --> 10:51.151
SHE SAYS, "MICHAEL,
YOU HAVE A GOOD HEART.

10:51.184 --> 10:53.053
"AND YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENS
TO A GOOD HEART?

10:53.086 --> 10:55.422
IT GETS THE S-H-I-T
KICKED OUT OF IT."

10:55.455 --> 10:57.825
- [chuckles]
SHE'S JUST KIDDING.

10:57.858 --> 10:59.927
- I THINK SHE SECRETLY WISHES
THAT I WAS MORE LIKE BRIAN.

10:59.960 --> 11:02.229
- NO HEART?

11:02.262 --> 11:04.698
ONE OF THE MOST IMPORTANT
QUALITIES A PERSON CAN HAVE

11:04.732 --> 11:06.700
IS A KIND AND LOVING NATURE.

11:06.734 --> 11:08.802
- I AGREE.

11:08.836 --> 11:12.205
IT'S DEFINITELY SOMETHING
WE INTEND TO INSTILL IN GUS.

11:12.239 --> 11:14.041
- AND SOMETHING WE WANT
OUR...

11:14.074 --> 11:16.710
SECOND CHILD
TO HAVE AS WELL.

11:16.744 --> 11:19.346
- YOU'RE HAVING ANOTHER KID?
- MM-HMM.

11:19.379 --> 11:21.114
- HEY, GUS,
MAKE ANOTHER HAPPY FACE!

11:21.148 --> 11:22.449
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
A BABY BROTHER...

11:22.482 --> 11:24.785
OR A BABY SISTER.

11:24.818 --> 11:28.455
- AND THIS TIME...
I'M GOING TO CARRY IT.

11:28.488 --> 11:29.723
- NO SHIT?

11:29.757 --> 11:30.991
- MAMA...
- SORRY.

11:31.024 --> 11:33.994
[laughter]
UM, THAT'S GREAT.

11:34.027 --> 11:36.129
- WHICH IS WHY WE ASKED YOU
TO STOP BY.

11:36.163 --> 11:37.965
- WHY,
YOU WANT ME TO BABY-SIT?

11:37.998 --> 11:40.834
- IT'S A LITTLE EARLY,
ISN'T IT?

11:44.104 --> 11:47.975
- WE'D LIKE YOU TO BE
THE FATHER.

11:48.008 --> 11:50.744
[baby babbles]

11:50.778 --> 11:53.513
- ME?

11:53.546 --> 11:55.448
- YEAH.

11:59.152 --> 12:02.355
- I THINK IT'S GREAT.

12:02.389 --> 12:03.824
- YOU DO?

12:03.857 --> 12:05.525
- WHAT, FATHERING A CHILD?

12:05.558 --> 12:08.261
HELPING MELANIE AND LINDSAY
CREATE A FAMILY?

12:08.295 --> 12:11.031
- BUT IT'S A BIG RESPONSIBILITY,
I MEAN, BRINGING A--

12:11.064 --> 12:13.033
A HUMAN BEING INTO THE WORLD,
YOU KNOW. I--

12:13.066 --> 12:15.836
I DON'T KNOW IF I'M READY TO BE
"THE OLD MAN," YOU KNOW?

12:15.869 --> 12:20.540
- UH...YOU ARE...

12:20.573 --> 12:23.844
MORE READY THAN YOU THINK.

12:23.877 --> 12:27.114
YOU WANNA SHOWER?

12:27.147 --> 12:29.917
HUH?

12:29.950 --> 12:32.052
- STILL, IT IS EXCITING,
THOUGH, ISN'T IT?

12:32.085 --> 12:34.855
I BETTER NOT FUCK IT UP.
- HOW COULD YOU FUCK IT UP?

12:34.888 --> 12:37.991
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO, MICHAEL,
IS...

12:38.025 --> 12:41.428
SUPPLY THE SPERM.

12:49.436 --> 12:51.471
- I WISH WE COULD HAVE ONE.

12:51.504 --> 12:55.075
- YEAH.
THAT'D BE A FIRST.

12:57.911 --> 12:59.880
- YOU COULD CARRY IT.

12:59.913 --> 13:01.348
- AND LOSE MY FIGURE?

13:01.381 --> 13:03.884
- FINE, I'LL CARRY IT.

13:03.917 --> 13:06.353
- I THINK YOU
HAVE BEEN WRITING TOO MANY

13:06.386 --> 13:12.359
FANTASTICAL ADVENTURES,
YOUNG MAN.

13:12.392 --> 13:16.529
- STILL, IT'S A NICE THOUGHT,
THOUGH, ISN'T IT?

13:34.147 --> 13:38.351
[video game beeping]

14:43.183 --> 14:45.652
- PUT IT BACK.

14:45.685 --> 14:48.521
I SAID, PUT IT BACK
IN THE FUCKING WALLET--NOW.

14:48.555 --> 14:50.123
- WHAT FOR?
YOU'VE GOT MORE MONEY

14:50.157 --> 14:51.391
THAN YOU KNOW
WHAT TO DO WITH.

14:51.424 --> 14:53.326
- WHO TOLD YOU THAT,
YOUR MOMMY?

14:53.360 --> 14:54.995
- SHE SAID YOU WERE
A SELFISH SON OF A BITCH

14:55.028 --> 14:56.997
WHO NEVER GAVE ANYONE
IN THIS FAMILY A RED CENT.

